snippet.textDisplay: I'm guessing you missed the news on the Steam Controller Linus. Valve seemingly screwed up and instead of stopping orders when they ran out continued to sell them for at least a day or more and are now cancelling orders. People will probably get refunds anyway, but it's worth noting that if you bought one on the 27th or later before they stopped selling it check your purchase history. Chances are you'll see it has been cancelled and will need to contact Valve to ensure you get a refund.
